obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (36323)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36323&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Company Limited`
  line `(Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1980.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sections 29 and 30 shall come into force at once and the remaining provisions of`
  line `this Act shall be deemed to have come into force on the 27th day of April, 1980.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (36324)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36324&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the 27th day of April, 1980;`
  line
  line `(b) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of Payments appointed under section 15;`
  line
  line `(c) "Company" means Messrs. National Company Limited, a company within the meaning`
  line `of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), and having its registered office at 18A-Brabourne Road,`
  line `Calcutta-700001, in the State of West Bengal;`
  line
  line `(d) "existing Government company" means a Government company which is carrying on`
  line `business on the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(e) "new Government company" means a Government company formed and registered on or after`
  line `the appointed day;`
  line
  line `(f) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "specified date", in relation to any provision of this Act, means such date as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, specify for the purposes of that provision and different dates may`
  line `be specified for different provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (36325)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government of the undertakings of the Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36325&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `On the appointed day, the undertakings of the Company, and the right, title and interest of`
  line `the Company in relation to its undertakings, shall, by virtue of this Act, stand transferred to, and vest in,`
  line `the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (36326)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `General effect of vesting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36326&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The undertakings of the Company shall be deemed to include all`
  line `assets, rights, lease-holds, powers, authorities and privileges, and all property, movable and immovable,`
  line `including lands, buildings, workshops, stores, instruments, machinery and equipment, cash balances, cash`
  line `on hand, reserve funds, investments, book debts and all other rights and interests in, or arising out of, such`
  line `property as were immediately before the appointed day in the ownership, possession, power or control of`
  line `the Company, whether within or outside India, and all books of account, registers and other documents of`
  line `whatever nature relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) All properties as aforesaid which have vested in the Central Government under section 3, shall, by`
  line `force of such vesting, be freed and discharged from any trust, obligation, mortgage, charge, lien and all`
  line `other incumbrances affecting them, and any attachment, injunction, decree or order of any Court or other`
  line `authority restricting the use of such properties in any manner or appointing any receiver in respect of the`
  line `whole or any part of such properties shall be deemed to have been withdrawn.`
  line
  line `(3) Every mortgagee of any property which has vested under this Act in the Central Government and`
  line `every person holding any charge, lien or other interest in, or in relation to, any such property shall give,`
  line `within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, an intimation to the Commissioner of such`
  line `mortgage, charge, lien or other interest.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the mortgagee of any property referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) or any other person holding any charge, lien or other interest in, or in relation to, any such`
  line `property shall be entitled to claim, in accordance with his rights and interests, payment of the mortgage`
  line `money or other dues, in whole or in part, out of the amounts specified in section 8 and also out of the`
  line `amounts determined under section 9, but no such mortgage, charge, lien or other interest shall be`
  line `enforceable against any property which has vested in the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Any licence or other instrument granted to the Company in relation to any undertaking which has`
  line `vested in the Central Government under section 3 at any time before the appointed day and in force`
  line `immediately before the appointed day shall continue to be in force on and after such day in accordance`
  line `with its tenor in relation to and for the purposes of such undertaking, and on and from the date of vesting`
  line `of such undertaking, under section 5, in an existing Government company, or under section 6, in a new`
  line `Government company, the existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, shall be deemed`
  line `to be substituted in such licence or other instrument as if such licence or other instrument had been`
  line `granted to such existing, or new, Government company and such existing, or new, Government company`
  line `shall hold it for the remainder of the period for which the Company would have held it under the terms`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(6) If, on the appointed day, any suit, appeal or other proceeding, of whatever nature, in relation to`
  line `any property which has vested in the Central Government under section 3, instituted or preferred by or`
  line `against the Company, is pending, the same shall not abate, be discontinued or be, in any way,`
  line `prejudicially affected by reason of the transfer of the undertakings of the Company, or of anything`
  line `contained in this Act, but the suit, appeal or other proceeding may be continued, prosecuted or enforced`
  line `by or against the Central Government, or where the undertakings of the Company are directed under`
  line `section 5, to vest in an existing Government company or become transferred by virtue of the provisions of`
  line `section 6 to a new Government company, by or against such Government company.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (36393)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of Central Government to direct vesting of the undertakings of the Company in an existing Government company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36393&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 3 and 4, and`
  line `subject to the provisions of section 6, the Central Government may, if it is satisfied that an existing`
  line `Government company is willing to comply, or has complied, with such terms and conditions as that`
  line `Government may think fit to impose, direct, by notification, that the undertakings of the Company, and`
  line `the right, title and interest of the Company in relation to its undertakings which have vested in the Central`
  line `Government under section 3, shall, instead of continuing to vest in the Central Government, vest in that`
  line `existing Government company either on the date of publication of the notification or on such earlier or`
  line `later date (not being a date earlier than the appointed day) as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the right, title and interest of the Company in relation to its undertakings vest, under`
  line `sub-section (1), in an existing Government company, that Government company shall, on and from the`
  line `date of such vesting be deemed to have become, and until the transfer of the undertakings by virtue of the`
  line `provisions of section 6, to a new Government company, be deemed to be, the owner in relation to such`
  line `undertakings and the rights and liabilities of the Central Government in relation to such undertakings`
  line `shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become, and until the date of such transfer,`
  line `be deemed to be, the rights and liabilities, respectively, of that existing Government company.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (36394)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Transfer of undertakings of the Company from an existing Government company to a new Government company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36394&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 3 and 4, where the`
  line `undertakings of the Company have been directed, under sub-section (1) of section 5, to vest in an existing`
  line `Government company, the Central Government may, if it is satisfied that a new Government company is`
  line `willing to comply, or has complied, with such terms and conditions as that Government may think fit to`
  line `impose, declare, by notification, that the undertakings of the Company be transferred to that new`
  line `Government company; and on the issue of such declaration, the right, title and interest of the Company in`
  line `relation to its undertakings, which had been directed under sub-section (1) of section 5 to vest in an`
  line `existing Government company, shall, instead of continuing to vest in that existing Government company,`
  line `vest in that new Government company with effect from the date on which such declaration is made.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the right, title and interest of the existing Government company in relation to the`
  line `undertakings of the Company vest under sub-section (1) in a new Government company, that new`
  line `Government company shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become the owner`
  line `in relation to such undertakings and the rights and liabilities of the existing Government company in`
  line `relation to such undertakings shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become the`
  line `rights and liabilities, respectively, of that new Government company.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (36329)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Company to be liable for certain prior liabilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36329&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every liability of the Company in respect`
  line `of any period prior to the appointed day, shall be the liability of the Company and shall be enforceable`
  line `against it, and not against the Central Government, or where the undertakings of the Company vest in an`
  line `existing, or a new, Government company, against such Government company.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that--`
  line
  line `(a) save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, no liability of the Company in relation to its`
  line `undertakings, in respect of any period prior to the appointed day, shall be enforceable against the`
  line `Central Government, or where the undertakings of the Company vest in an existing, or a new,`
  line `Government company, against such Government company;`
  line
  line `(b) no award, decree or order of any court, tribunal or other authority in relation to the`
  line `undertakings of the Company, passed after the appointed day in respect of any matter, claim or`
  line `dispute, which arose before that day, shall be enforceable against the Central Government, or where`
  line `the undertakings of the Company vest in an existing, or a new, Government company, against such`
  line `Government company;`
  line
  line `(c) no liability incurred by the Company before the appointed day for the contravention of any`
  line `provision of law for the time being in force shall be enforceable against the Central Government, or`
  line `where the undertakings of the Company vest in an existing, or a new, Government company, against`
  line `such Government company.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (36330)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36330&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government, under`
  line `section 3, of the undertakings of the Company, and the right, title and interest of the Company in relation`
  line `to such undertakings, there shall be given by the Central Government to the Company in cash and in the`
  line `manner specified in Chapter VI, an amount of rupees ten crores and four lakhs.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the liabilities of the Company, in relation to`
  line `its undertakings, shall be met, in accordance with the rights and interests of the creditors of the Company,`
  line `from the amount due to the Company under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (36331)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Payment of further amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36331&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the deprivation of the Company of the management of the`
  line `undertakings owned by it, there shall be given, by the Central Government, to the Company, in addition`
  line `to the amount specified in section 8, an amount computed at the rate of ten thousand rupees per annum for`
  line `the period commencing on the date on which the management of the undertakings of the Company was`
  line `taken over in pursuance of the order made by the Central Government under section 18AA of the`
  line `Industries (Development and Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951), and ending on the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount specified in section 8, and the amount computed in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1), shall carry simple interest at the rate of four per cent. per annum for the period`
  line `commencing on the appointed day and ending on the date on which payment of such amount is made by`
  line `the Central Government to the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) The amounts determined in accordance with the provisions of sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be`
  line `given to the Company in addition to the amount specified in section 8.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (36332)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Management, etc., of the undertakings of the Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36332&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The general superintendence,`
  line `direction, control and management of the affairs and business of the undertakings owned by the`
  line `Company, the right, title and interest in relation to which have vested in the Central Government under`
  line `section 3, shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) where a direction has been made by the Central Government under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 5, vest, on and from the date, specified in such direction, in the existing Government company`
  line `specified therein; or`
  line
  line `(b) where a declaration has been made under sub-section (1) of section 6, vest, on and from the`
  line `date of such declaration, in the new Government company specified therein; or`
  line
  line `(c) where no direction referred to in clause (a) or declaration referred to in clause (b) has been`
  line `made, vest, on and from the appointed day, in one or more Custodians appointed by the Central`
  line `Government under sub-section (2),`
  line
  line `and thereupon the existing, or new, Government company or the Custodian or Custodians so appointed,`
  line `as the case may be, shall be entitled to exercise, to the exclusion of all other persons, all such powers and`
  line `do all such things as the Company is authorised to exercise and do in relation to the undertakings owned`
  line `by it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint one or more individuals or a Government company as the`
  line `Custodian or Custodians of the undertakings of the Company in relation to which no direction has been`
  line `made by it under sub-section (1) of section 5 or no declaration has been made by it under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 6, and the Custodian or Custodians so appointed shall receive, from the funds of the`
  line `undertakings, such remuneration as may be specified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Custodian or Custodians of the undertakings of the Company shall maintain an account of the`
  line `undertakings of the Company in such form and manner and under such conditions as may be prescribed,`
  line `and the provisions of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), shall apply to the audit of the accounts so`
  line `maintained as they apply to the audit of the accounts of a company.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (36395)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Duty of persons in charge of management of the undertakings of the Company to deliver all assets, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36395&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the vesting of the management of the undertakings of the Company in an existing, or`
  line `a new, Government company or on the appointment of a Custodian or Custodians, all persons in charge of`
  line `the management of the undertakings of the Company immediately before such vesting or appointment`
  line `shall be bound to deliver to such Government company, or the Custodian or Custodians, as the case may`
  line `be, all assets, books of account, registers and other documents in their custody relating to the undertakings`
  line `of the Company.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may issue such directions as it may deem desirable in the circumstances`
  line `of the case to the existing, or new, Government company or the Custodian or Custodians, and such`
  line `Government company, Custodian or Custodians may also, if it is considered necessary so to do, apply to`
  line `the Central Government at any time for instructions as to the manner in which the management of the`
  line `undertakings of the Company shall be conducted or in relation to any other matter arising in the course of`
  line `such management.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (36334)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Duty of persons to account for assets, etc., in their possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36334&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who has, on`
  line `the appointed day, in his possession or under his control, any assets, books, documents or other papers`
  line `relating to any undertaking owned by the Company, which has vested in the Central Government or in an`
  line `existing, or a new, Government company under this Act, and which belongs to the Company, or would`
  line `have so belonged, if the undertakings owned by the Company had not vested in the Central Government`
  line `or such Government company, shall be liable to account for the said assets, books, documents and other`
  line `papers to the Central Government or the Government company and shall deliver them up to the Central`
  line `Government or such Government company or to such person or body of persons as the Central`
  line `Government or the Government company may specify in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may take or cause to be taken all necessary steps for securing possession`
  line `of the undertakings of the Company which have vested in it under section 3.`
  line
  line `(3) The Company shall, within such period as the Central Government may allow in this behalf,`
  line `furnish to that Government a complete inventory of all its property and assets, as on the appointed day,`
  line `pertaining to the undertakings which have vested in the Central Government under section 3, and, for this`
  line `purpose, the Central Government or the existing, or new, Government company shall afford to the`
  line `Company all reasonable facilities.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (36335)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Continuance of employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36335&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every employee of the Company in connection with any`
  line `undertaking owned by it, shall become, on and from the appointed day, an employee of the Central`
  line `Government, and where such undertaking is vested in an existing, or a new, Government company under`
  line `this Act, become, on and from the date of such vesting in such Government company, an employee`
  line `thereof and shall hold office or service under the Central Government or the existing, of new,`
  line `Government company, as the case may be, with the same rights and privileges as to pension, gratuity and`
  line `other matters as would have been admissible to him if there had been no such vesting and shall continue`
  line `to do so unless and until his employment under the Central Government or the existing, or new,`
  line `Government company, as the case may be, is duly terminated or until his remuneration and other`
  line `conditions of service are duly altered by the Central Government or the existing, or new, Government`
  line `company, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the lime being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other person employed`
  line `in any undertakings owned by the Company to the Central Government or the existing, or new,`
  line `Government company shall not entitle such officer or other employee to any compensation under this Act`
  line `or any other law for the time being in force and no such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal`
  line `or other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (36336)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Provident fund and other funds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36336&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Company has established a provident fund,`
  line `superannuation fund, welfare fund or other fund for the benefit of persons employed in any of the`
  line `undertakings owned by it, the monies relatable to the employees, whose services have become transferred`
  line `by or under this Act to the Central Government or an existing, or a new, Government company shall, out`
  line `of the monies standing, on the appointed day, to the credit of such provident fund, superannuation fund,`
  line `welfare fund or other fund, stand transferred to, and shall vest in, the Central Government or the`
  line `Government company, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The monies which stand transferred under sub-section (1) to the Central Government or the`
  line `existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, shall be dealt with by that Government or the`
  line `Government company in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (36337)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Appointment of Commissioner of Payments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36337&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, for the`
  line `purpose of disbursing the amounts payable under sections 8 and 9 to the Company, by notification,`
  line `appoint a Commissioner of Payments.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may appoint such other persons as it may think fit to assist the`
  line `Commissioner and thereupon the Commissioner may authorise one or more of such persons also to`
  line `exercise all or any of the powers exercisable by him under this Act and different persons may be`
  line `authorised to exercise different powers.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person authorised by the Commissioner to exercise any of the powers exercisable by the`
  line `Commissioner may exercise those powers in the same manner and with the same effect as if they have`
  line `been conferred on that person directly by this Act and not by way of authorisation.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances of the Commissioner and other persons appointed under this section`
  line `shall be defrayed out of the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (36338)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Payment by the Central Government to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36338&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government`
  line `shall, within thirty days from the specified date, pay, in cash, to the Commissioner, for payment to the`
  line Company--
  line
  line `(a) an amount equal to that specified in section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) a further amount equal to the amount payable to the Company under section 9.`
  line
  line `(2) A deposit account shall be opened by the Central Government in favour of the Commissioner, in`
  line `the Public Account of India, and every amount paid under this Act to the Commissioner shall be`
  line `deposited by him to the credit of the said deposit account and the said deposit account shall be operated`
  line `by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(3) Records shall be maintained by the Commissioner in respect of the undertakings of the Company`
  line `in relation to which payment has been made to him under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Interest accruing on the amounts standing to the credit of the deposit account referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) shall ensure to the benefit of the Company.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (36339)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Certain powers of the Central Government or Government company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36339&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government or the existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, shall be entitled to`
  line `receive up to the specified date, to the exclusion of all other persons, any money due to the Company, in`
  line `relation to any of the undertakings owned by it which have vested in the Central Government or such`
  line `Government company, and realised after the appointed day, notwithstanding that the realisation pertains`
  line `to a period prior to the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government or the existing, or new, Government company, as the case may be, may`
  line `make a claim to the Commissioner with regard to every payment made by that Government or`
  line `Government company, after the appointed day, for discharging any liability of the Company in respect of`
  line `any of the undertakings owned by it, in relation to any period prior to the appointed day; and every such`
  line `claim shall have priority in accordance with the priorities attaching under this Act, to the matter in`
  line `relation to which such liability has been discharged by the Central Government or the Government`
  line company.
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the liabilities of the Company in relation to any of the`
  line `undertakings owned by it, in respect of any transaction prior to the appointed day, which have not been`
  line `discharged on or before the specified date, shall be the liabilities of the Company.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (36340)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Claims to be made to the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36340&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every person having a claim against the Company`
  line `with regard to any of the matters specified in the Schedule, pertaining to any undertaking owned by it,`
  line `shall prefer such claim before the Commissioner within thirty days from the specified date:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Commissioner is satisfied that the claimant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from preferring the claim within the said period of thirty days, he may entertain the claim within a further`
  line `period of thirty days, but not thereafter.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (36341)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Priority of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36341&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The claims made under section 18 shall have priorities in accordance with`
  line `the following principles, namely:`
  line
  line `(a) Category I shall have precedence over all other categories and Category II shall have`
  line `precedence over Category III and so on;`
  line
  line `(b) the claims specified in each of the categories shall rank equally and be paid in full, but, if the`
  line `amount is insufficient to meet such claims in full, they shall abate in equal proportions and be paid`
  line `accordingly; and`
  line
  line `(c) the question of discharging any liability with regard to a matter specified in a lower category`
  line `shall arise only if a surplus is left after meeting all the liabilities specified in the immediately higher`
  line category.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (36342)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Examination of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36342&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of the claims made under section 18, the Commissioner`
  line `shall arrange the claims in the order of priorities specified in the Schedule and examine the same in`
  line `accordance with such order.`
  line
  line `(2) If, on examination of the claims, the Commissioner is of opinion that the amount paid to him`
  line `under this Act is not sufficient to meet the liabilities specified in any lower category, he shall not be`
  line `required to examine any claim in respect of such lower category.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (36343)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Admission or rejection of claims.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36343&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) After examining the claims with reference to the`
  line `priorities set out in the Schedule, the Commissioner shall fix a date on or before which every claimant`
  line `shall file the proof of his claim.`
  line
  line `(2) Not less than fourteen days' notice of the date so fixed shall be given by advertisement in one`
  line `issue of any daily newspaper in the English language having circulation in the major part of the country`
  line `and one issue of any daily newspaper in such regional language as the Commissioner may consider`
  line `suitable, and every such notice shall call upon the claimant to file the proof of his claim with the`
  line `Commissioner within the period specified in the advertisement.`
  line
  line `(3) Every claimant who fails to file the proof of his claim within the period specified by the`
  line `Commissioner shall be excluded from the disbursement made by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commissioner shall, after such investigation as may, in his opinion, be necessary and after`
  line `giving the Company an opportunity of refuting the claim and after giving the claimant a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard, by order in writing, admit or reject the claim in whole or in part.`
  line
  line `(5) The Commissioner shall have the power to regulate his own procedure in all matters arising out of`
  line `the discharge of his functions, including the place or places at which he may hold his sitting and shall, for`
  line `the purpose of making any investigation under this Act, have the same powers as are vested in a civil`
  line `court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the summoning and enforcing the attendance of any witness and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) the discovery and production of any document or other material object producible as`
  line evidence;
  line
  line `(c) the reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) the issuing of any commission for the examination of witnesses.`
  line
  line `(6) Any investigation before the Commissioner shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Commissioner shall be`
  line `deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(7) A claimant who is dissatisfied with the decision of the Commissioner may prefer an appeal`
  line `against such decision to the High Court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction the registered office`
  line `of the Company is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a person who is a Judge of a High Court is appointed to be the Commissioner,`
  line `such appeal shall be heard and disposed of by not less than two Judges of that High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (36344)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Disbursement of money by the Commissioner.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36344&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `After admitting a claim under this Act, the`
  line `amount due in respect of such claim shall be paid by the Commissioner to the person or persons to whom`
  line `such amount is due and on such payment, the liability of the Company in respect of any claim relating to`
  line `the undertakings owned by it shall stand discharged.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (36345)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Disbursement of amounts to the Company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36345&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) If out of the monies paid to him in relation to`
  line `any undertaking owned by the Company there is a balance left after meeting the liabilities as specified in`
  line `the Schedule, the Commissioner shall disburse such balance to the Company.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the possession of any machinery, equipment or other property has vested in the Central`
  line `Government or any existing, or new, Government company under this Act, but such machinery,`
  line `equipment or other property does not belong to the Company, it shall be lawful for the Central`
  line `Government or, as the case may be, the existing, or new, Government company, to continue to possess`
  line `such machinery or equipment or other property on the same terms and conditions under which they were`
  line `possessed by the Company, immediately before the appointed day.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (36346)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Undisbursed or unclaimed amount to be deposited with the general revenue account.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36346&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line Any
  line `money paid to the Commissioner which remains undisbursed or unclaimed on the date immediately`
  line `preceding the date on which the office of the Commissioner is finally would up, shall be transferred by`
  line `the Commissioner, before his office is finally wound up, to the general revenue account of the Central`
  line `Government; but a claim to any money so transferred may be preferred to the Central Government by the`
  line `person entitled to such payment and shall be dealt with as if such transfer had not been made, and the`
  line `order, if any, for payment of the claim being treated as an order for the refund of revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (36347)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36347&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law, other than this Act, or in any decree or order of any court, tribunal or`
  line `other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (36348)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Assumption of liability.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36348&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any liability of the Company arising out of any item`
  line `specified in any category in Part I of the Schedule is not discharged fully by the Commissioner out of the`
  line `amounts paid to him under this Act, the Commissioner shall intimate in writing to the Central`
  line `Government the extent of the liability which remains undischarged and that liability shall be assumed by`
  line `the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by order, direct the existing, or new, Government company in`
  line `which the undertakings of the Company become vested by virtue of any direction made under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 5 or declaration made under sub-section (1) of section 6, to take over the liability assumed`
  line `by the Central Government under sub-section (1), and on receipt of such direction, it shall be the duty of`
  line `such existing, or new, Government company to discharge such liability.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (36349)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Management to continue to vest in the Custodian until alternative arrangements have been made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36349&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding the vesting under this Act of the undertakings of the Company in the Central`
  line `Government or an existing, or a new, Government company,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Custodian who has been managing the affairs of such undertaking before the date on`
  line `which the undertaking had so vested shall, until alternative arrangements have been made by the`
  line `Central Government or, as the case may be, such Government company, for the management of such`
  line `undertakings continue to manage the affairs of the undertakings, as if the Custodian had been`
  line `authorised by the Central Government or, as the case may be, such Government company, to manage`
  line `such undertakings;`
  line
  line `(b) the Custodian or any person authorised by him for this purpose shall, until alternative`
  line `arrangements have been made by the Central Government or, as the case may be, such Government`
  line `company, continue to be authorised to operate, in relation to the undertakings of the Company, any`
  line `account of such undertakings in any bank as if the Custodian or the person authorised by him had`
  line `been authorised by the Central Government or such Government company to operate such account.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (36396)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Contracts to cease to have effect unless ratified by the Central Government or the Government company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36396&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Every contract entered into by the Company in relation to any of the`
  line `undertakings owned by it, which has vested in the Central Government under section 3, for any service,`
  line `sale or supply and in force immediately before the appointed day, shall, on and from the expiry of a`
  line `period of one hundred and eighty days from the appointed day, cease to have effect unless such contract`
  line `is, before the expiry of that period, ratified, in writing, by the Central Government, or the existing, or`
  line `new, Government company, in which such undertakings have been vested under this Act, and in ratifying`
  line `such contract the Central Government or such Government company may make such alteration or`
  line `modification therein as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government or such Government company shall not omit to ratify a`
  line `contract and shall not make any alteration or modification in a contract--`
  line
  line `(a) unless it is satisfied that such contract is unduly onerous or has been entered into in bad faith`
  line `or is detrimental to the interests of the Central Government or such Government company; and`
  line
  line `(b) except after giving the parties to the contract a reasonable opportunity of being heard and`
  line `except after recording in writing its reasons for refusal to ratify the contract or for making any`
  line `alteration or modification therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (36351)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36351&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) having in his possession, custody or control any property forming part of the undertakings`
  line `owned by the Company, wrongfully withholds such property from the Central Government or the`
  line `Government company; or`
  line
  line `(b) wrongfully obtains possession of, or retains, any property forming part of, the undertakings`
  line `owned by the Company; or`
  line
  line `(c) wilfully withholds or fails to furnish to the Central Government or the existing, or new,`
  line `Government company or any person or body of persons specified by that Government or such`
  line `Government company, as the case may be, any document relating to the undertakings owned by the`
  line `Company, which may be in his possession, custody or control; or`
  line
  line `(d) fails to deliver to the Central Government or the existing, or new, Government company or`
  line `any person or body of persons specified by that Government or Government company, any assets,`
  line `books of account, registers or other documents in his possession, custody or control relating to the`
  line `undertakings owned by the Company; or`
  line
  line `(e) wrongfully removes or destroys any property forming part of the undertakings owned by the`
  line `Company or prefers any claim under this Act which he knows or has reason to believe to be false or`
  line `grossly inaccurate,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and also with fine which`
  line `may extend to ten thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (36352)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36352&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (36353)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36353&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or any officer of that Government or the existing, or new,`
  line `Government company in which the undertakings of the Company have vested under this Act or other`
  line `person authorised by that Government or Government company for anything which is in good faith done`
  line `or intended to be done under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or any of its officers or`
  line `other employees or the existing, or new, Government company aforesaid or any officer or other person`
  line `authorised by that Company for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good`
  line `faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (36354)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36354&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, direct that all or any`
  line `of the powers exercisable by it under this Act, other than the powers conferred by this section and`
  line `sections 33 and 34, may also be exercised by such person or persons as may be specified in the`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any delegation of power is made under sub-section (1), the person to whom such power`
  line `has been delegated shall act under the direction, control and supervision of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (36355)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36355&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, makes rules for`
  line `carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time within which, and the manner in which, an intimation referred to in sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 4 shall be given;`
  line
  line `(b) the form and manner in which and the conditions under which accounts shall be maintained`
  line `by the Custodian or Custodians, as required by sub-section (3) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which the monies in any provident fund or other fund, referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 14, shall be dealt with;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (36356)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36356&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the appointed`
  line day.
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (36357)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814&sectionId=36357&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_00008_198042_1517807325814
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Company Limited (Acquisition and Transfer of`
  line `Undertakings) Ordinance, 1980 (4 of 1980), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the Ordinance so repealed`
  line `shall be deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
